gomodel:SYNGO_5515  a     owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Rationale: Figure 1, S1: Confocal imaging of FUS in mouse cortex and hippocampus showed localization to along dendrites and axons as well as association with synaptic markers Synapsin-1 (SYN1) and PSD95 (DLG4).\n\nFigure 1c,d: sub-synaptic localization of FUS was determined using STED superresolution microscopy. Synaptic FUS preferentially associates with excitatory synapses, of which 46% contained FUS, while only 20% of analyzed inhibitory synapses showed FUS positivity.\n\nFigure 1h: The majority of FUS was found localized to the presynaptic terminal, approx 150nm from the active zone, but postsynaptic localization (away from the PSD) was also observed.. Experimental description: Results: \"To clarify the precise localization of FUS at the synapses, we first performed confocal analysis in mouse cortex (Fig. 1a, b) and hippocampus (Supplementary Fig. 1a, b)\"\n\nantibodies;\nFUS Rb, Bethyl, A300-293A\nFUS Rb, Bethyl, A300-294A\nFUS Ms, 4H11, Santa CruZ, sc-47711" ;
        lego:modelstate   "production" ;
        dc:contributor    "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-4973-5732" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-2286-1587" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-2514-0216" ;
        dc:date           "2023-11-02" ;
        dc:title          "SYNGO_CC_5515" ;
        pav:providedBy    "https://syngo.vu.nl" ;
        biolink:in_taxon  "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/NCBITaxon_10090" .

